5. CRITICAL BUGS: null reference risks, unhandled promise rejections, infinite loops, memory leaks
6. ASSET/STYLE LOADING CHAIN: Trace the path from entry point to every stylesheet, asset, or config that the project depends on. If any file uses utility classes (Tailwind, Bootstrap, etc.), verify the framework's CSS is actually imported somewhere in the dependency chain starting from the entry point. If fonts, icons, or images are referenced, verify they exist or are loaded from a valid CDN. Flag as CRITICAL if any styling framework is used in components but never imported.
7. BUILD & RUN CHAIN: Can this project actually build and start? Verify: (a) the entry point referenced in the HTML or config exists, (b) the package manager config (package.json, requirements.txt, go.mod, Cargo.toml, etc.) lists ALL dependencies used in source files, (c) build/dev scripts exist and reference valid tooling, (d) all config files use a consistent module format (no mixing ESM exports with CommonJS require in the same project unless explicitly supported).
