Source: https://github.com/pmndrs/zustand/blob/main/docs/reference/previous-versions/zustand-v3-create-context.md

This example illustrates a more complete application of `createContext` within a React component hierarchy. It defines a Zustand store with state and actions, then uses the `Provider` to make this store available to child components. The `useStore` hook is used in a child component to access and modify the store's state, demonstrating a common pattern for state management.

